DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,9,1);
$k = random(4,9,1);

$aa = $a*$a;
$n = 2*$k + 3;
$m = 2*$k + 1;
$p = 2*$k;

$answer = "($a/$m) * (x^2/($aa - x^2))**($m/2)";


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Evaluate the indefinite integral
$PAR 
\(\displaystyle\int \frac{ {$a}^3 x^{$p} \, dx}{($aa - x^2)^{$n/2}} \)
= \{ans_rule( 50) \} \( \ + \ C \)

Hint: The easiest way to evaluate the trig integral is to turn sine and cosine into tangent and secant.

EOT

&HINT(EV3(<<'EOT'));
Make a trigonometric substitution.  To solve the resulting
integral, remember that \( (\sin x)/(\cos x) = \tan x \)
and that \( 1/(\cos x) = \sec x \).
EOT

ANS(fun_cmp($answer, domain=>[0.4*$a,0.6*$a], mode=>"antider"));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
